    "description": {
      "value": "<div class=\"ariadne-entry\"><p><strong>Source:</strong> Ariadne's Book of Legends - Alpha v1.2, p. 58-61.</p><p>Incapacitating Strike</p><p>When you reach 20th level, you learn to channel your hunting prowess into a lethal, debilitating strike. You can use your action and expend 1 Legendary Point to make an attack roll against a creature within range. On a hit, you deal your normal weapon damage plus 40 Lethal damage, and the target must succeed on a Constitution saving throw against your spell save DC. On a failure, the target is incapacitated for a minute. If the creature is immune to the incapacitated condition, it is impaired instead. A creature can repeat the saving throw at the end of each of its turns, ending the effect on itself on a success.</p><p>— Spell Slots Per</p><p>Favored</p><p>Prepared</p><p>Spell Level — 1st 2nd 3rd 4th 5th</p><p>Enemy</p><p>Points</p><p>Spells</p><p>1 6 16 4 3 3 3 2</p><p>2 7 17 4 3 3 3 2</p><p>3 7 18 4 3 3 3 2</p></div>",
